### insertIntoScope() {#a6dbb41fd5cc8c3a1aec830d3e6cd232e}

<MemberDefinition
  template={<>template &lt;typename K, typename V, typename KInfo, typename AllocatorTy&gt;</>}
  prototype={<>void llvm::ScopedHashTable&lt; K, V, KInfo, AllocatorTy &gt;::insertIntoScope (<a href="#a916447ffc6b1b42def2dc801e65d5834">ScopeTy</a> &#42; S, <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> K &amp; Key, <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> V &amp; Val)</>}
  labels = {["inline"]}>
insertIntoScope - This inserts the specified key/value at the specified (possibly not the current) scope.

While it is ok to insert into a scope that isn&#39;t the current one, it isn&#39;t ok to insert <em>underneath</em> an existing value of the specified key.
